{"actor":"Ryan Snodgrass","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-05T19:02:30Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":115,"issue_id":"ox-hwe","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"ox-hwe\",\"title\":\"Track cumulative context consumption per agent instance\",\"description\":\"Track how many tokens/chars ox commands whisper into each agent's context window on a per-agent-ID basis. Each ox command that produces stdout (prime, query, team-ctx, session list) should add its output size to a running counter in the agent instance record. This enables: (1) visibility into how much context budget ox consumes vs the agent's working memory, (2) ox status/doctor can surface the metric, (3) product decisions about when to compress output harder. The agent instance JSONL already tracks prime_call_count — extend with context_chars or similar.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"feature\",\"owner\":\"ryan@sageox.ai\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T02:29:46Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ryan Snodgrass\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T02:29:46Z\"}"}
