{"actor":"Ryan Snodgrass","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-06T10:00:14Z","event_type":"claimed","id":119,"issue_id":"ox-nas","new_value":"{\"assignee\":\"Ryan Snodgrass\",\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"ox-nas\",\"title\":\"Fix ox doctor complaints after fresh ox init\",\"description\":\"After running ox init in a fresh git repo, ox doctor shows 7 warnings and 1 failure. Root causes: (1) init staging race — files modified after staging, (2) doctor git auth false positive — ox uses PAT auth not credential helper, (3) ledger push failure during daemon bootstrap, (4) noisy post-init warnings. Tests don't catch this because they either cheat (commit before doctor) or filter out every failure.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":1,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"ryan@sageox.ai\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-06T18:00:10Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ryan Snodgrass\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-06T18:00:10Z\"}"}
